SSyynnooppssiiss
       cc [flag . . .] file -lmenu -locurses [library . . .]

       #include <menu.h>

       int    set_menu_mark(MENU   *menu,   char   *mark);   char
       *menu_mark(MENU *menu);

DDeessccrriippttiioonn
       menus displays mark strings to distinguish selected  items
       in  a  menu (or the current item in a single-valued menu).
       set_menu_mark sets  the  mark  string  of  menu  to  mark.
       menu_mark returns a pointer to the mark string of menu.

 vvaalluuee
       menu_mark  returns  NULL  on error.  set_menu_mark returns
       one of the following:
       ----------------------------------------------------------------------
       E_OK             -   The routine returned successfully.
       E_SYSTEM_ERROR   -   System error.
       E_BAD_ARGUMENT   -   An incorrect argument was passed to the routine.

NNoottiicceess
       The header file menu.h automatically includes  the  header
       files eti.h and ocurses.h.

       The mark string cannot be NULL.

